cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper involves computer vision techniques such as deep learning-based instance segmentation and classification, as well as robotics-related applications such as SLAM (Simultaneous Localization and Mapping). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves robotics-related applications, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep learning techniques suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the proposed modifications to the registration cost function suggest that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves 3D mapping, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GR (Graphics).
